classes.title: INTRO UNDERGR RSRCH
classes.description: Introduces students to viewing themselves as active members of an intellectual community.   This course introduces students to research processes across the academic disciplines,   developing a familiarity with various methodologies. Lectures and TA sections explore the   nature of modern research and creative activities with an emphasis on how undergraduates   can participate. Students develop a tangible understanding of how to become undergraduate   researchers and research assistants. Designed for first-generation college students.

classes.title: RECOVERING STORIES
classes.description: The Black Lives Matter movement has shown how structural inequalities in ou r contemporary US society have created distinctly different experiences for minoritized communities. This problem is not unique to our contemporary wo rld. In our understanding of global history, many voices have been overlook ed. How can we understand histories of ancient societies that did not leave a written record? This course examines the ways in which researchers recon struct histories of ignored and forgotten communities from the ancient to c ontemporary world today. We also consider what communities have been overlo oked in our local Santa Barbara history and what means we have to reconstru ct these histories.

classes.title: WORD MAGAZINE
classes.description: This course produces a quarterly magazine committed to exploring and improving cultural life   in Isla Vista. Working under professional deadlines, students complete writing, design, or   layout assignments in their areas of expertise. Active participation in distribution, ad sales, event planning, and editing allows for a well-rounded experience in print magazine   production. Attendance at all scheduled classes is mandatory.

classes.title: INT HUMANITIES
classes.description: This creative writing workshop is for veterans who wish to write about thei r military experiences. Participants will share and discuss their work with each other in an informal setting.
